 It's a psalm.

773
00:57:23,000 --> 00:57:29,000
 So Jesus was led by the Psalms,

774
00:57:29,000 --> 00:57:33,000
 even how to bring his agony and his grief and his pain to the Father.

775
00:57:33,000 --> 00:57:39,000
 And so we're going to see how the psalm invites us to bring those things that are heavy,

776
00:57:39,000 --> 00:57:41,000
 where a lot of times we don't know what to do,

777
00:57:41,000 --> 00:57:45,000
 to the God, and to see how God meets us when we do that.

778
00:57:46,000 --> 00:57:51,000
 So we're in Psalm 6, and starting in verse 1 it says this,

779
00:57:51,000 --> 00:57:56,000
 "Lord, do not rebuke me in your anger, or discipline me in your wrath.

780
00:57:56,000 --> 00:58:00,000
 Have mercy on me, Lord, for I am faint.

781
00:58:00,000 --> 00:58:04,000
 Heal me, Lord, my bones are in agony.

782
00:58:04,000 --> 00:58:07,000
 My soul is in deep anguish.

783
00:58:07,000 --> 00:58:11,000
 How long? How long?

784
00:58:12,000 --> 00:58:14,000
 How often?

785
00:58:14,000 --> 00:58:16,000
 How often?

786
00:58:16,000 --> 00:58:20,000
 When we go through painful and difficult things,

787
00:58:20,000 --> 00:58:24,000
 there's a thought that comes up in our hearts and minds,

788
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:28,000
 and we wonder, "Is somehow God angry at us?

789
00:58:28,000 --> 00:58:33,000
 Is he somehow disciplining us or punishing us?"

790
00:58:33,000 --> 00:58:36,000
 And we wonder about that.

791
00:58:36,000 --> 00:58:38,000
 I don't know if you've ever thought of that.

792
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:40,000
 I have thought of that.

793
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:44,000
 I have thought of that as I've gone through painful experiences.

794
00:58:44,000 --> 00:58:46,000
 Is God somehow disciplining me?

795
00:58:46,000 --> 00:58:49,000
 Is there a sin that I need to confess, something that I need to sort out?

796
00:58:49,000 --> 00:58:52,000
 And sometimes there might be, you know, where there's something we need to work out,

797
00:58:52,000 --> 00:58:55,000
 but a lot of times we just don't know.

798
00:58:55,000 --> 00:58:59,000
 And we feel like maybe there's a distance, and we're just wondering what's going on.

799
00:58:59,000 --> 00:59:05,000
 Well, here in the Psalm, David, he doesn't confess any very specific sin.

800
00:59:05,000 --> 00:59:09,000
 He does that in others where he's clear.

801
00:59:09,000 --> 00:59:14,000
 So it seems that David is like, "Lord, I don't know if I did something wrong.

802
00:59:14,000 --> 00:59:18,000
 Lord, do not rebuke me in your anger or discipline me in your wrath.

803
00:59:18,000 --> 00:59:23,000
 Take this away. This burden is too heavy."

804
00:59:23,000 --> 00:59:25,000
 The psalmist describes the circumstances.

805
00:59:25,000 --> 00:59:29,000
 "For I am faint. My bones are in agony.

806
00:59:29,000 --> 00:59:33,000
 My soul is in deep anguish."

807
00:59:33,000 --> 00:59:45,000
 Now, throughout the Psalms, pain and suffering is described as physical suffering and pain.

808
00:59:45,000 --> 00:59:49,000
 But it doesn't mean that it just refers to physical suffering and pain.

809
00:59:49,000 --> 00:59:57,000
 Actually, a lot of times it's used as a metaphor to also talk about emotional suffering and pain.

810
00:59:57,000 --> 01:00:04,000
 And so we actually don't know the circumstance that triggered this pain and suffering in David's life.

811
01:00:04,000 --> 01:00:09,000
 If it's an illness or if it's something emotional, something else has happened.

812
01:00:09,000 --> 01:00:12,000
 We don't know.

813
01:00:12,000 --> 01:00:17,000
 But this is a cry, "I can't take it any longer.

814
01:00:17,000 --> 01:00:20,000
 Do something.

815
01:00:20,000 --> 01:00:27,000
 My circumstances, they're weighing me down and they're crushing me.

816
01:00:27,000 --> 01:00:31,000
 How long?

817
01:00:31,000 --> 01:00:38,000
 How long?"

818
01:00:38,000 --> 01:00:45,000
 Now, that's the cry of someone who is at the end of the ropes.

819
01:00:45,000 --> 01:00:53,000
 But it is also the cry of someone who is hoping God will act.

820
01:00:53,000 --> 01:00:58,000
 So by crying out to God and asking God how long, David is expressing his hope,

821
01:00:58,000 --> 01:01:06,000
 even if it is a faint hope, that God can step in and change his circumstances.

822
01:01:06,000 --> 01:01:11,000
 So I lament as a complaint to God, as a complaint to the one we believe

823
01:01:11,000 --> 01:01:18,000
 who can actually do something about what's going on.

824
01:01:18,000 --> 01:01:22,000
 And this element of hope is important because when we cry out,

825
01:01:22,000 --> 01:01:26,000
 we come to the one who can actually help.

826
01:01:26,000 --> 01:01:30,000
 We come to the one who can meet us and deliver us,

827
01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:40,000
 who can show us mercy, who can lift us out of whatever difficulty it is that we're facing.

828
01:01:40,000 --> 01:01:46,000
 Now, ultimately, this is a plea for God's mercy.

829
01:01:46,000 --> 01:01:51,000
 You see it in verse 2, "Have mercy on me."

830
01:01:51,000 --> 01:01:56,000
 There's an Old Testament professor I like, and he comments on this verse.

831
01:01:56,000 --> 01:02:00,000
 He says this, "When people in life are against us,

832
01:02:00,000 --> 01:02:05,000
 we have nothing to turn to but God's generosity,

833
01:02:05,000 --> 01:02:10,000
 his grace, his mercy, his love.

834
01:02:10,000 --> 01:02:13,000
 He's the one that delivers us. He's the one that meets us.

835
01:02:13,000 --> 01:02:18,000
 He's the one that has the power to bring us out, to bring us through,

836
01:02:18,000 --> 01:02:27,000
 to sustain us when we are weak, when we have nothing left in our tank.

837
01:02:27,000 --> 01:02:33,000
 Let's continue. Verse 4, "Turn, Lord, and deliver me.

838
01:02:33,000 --> 01:02:37,000
 Save me because of your unfailing love.

839
01:02:37,000 --> 01:02:41,000
 Among the dead, no one proclaims your name.

840
01:02:41,000 --> 01:02:45,000
 Who praises you from this grave?"

841
01:02:45,000 --> 01:02:49,000
 Now, the word that's translated as "turn,"

842
01:02:49,000 --> 01:02:53,000
 actually a more literal translation is "return."

843
01:02:53,000 --> 01:02:56,000
 So David is saying, "Return to me, Lord."

844
01:02:56,000 --> 01:02:59,000
 He feels like God has abandoned him.

845
01:02:59,000 --> 01:03:03,000
 He feels like he's on his own.

846
01:03:03,000 --> 01:03:09,000
 "Return to me."

847
01:03:09,000 --> 01:03:19,000
 And he also appeals to God's love, to his unfailing love.

848
01:03:19,000 --> 01:03:27,000
 So when we lament, we also call on who God is and who he promises to be.

849
01:03:27,000 --> 01:03:33,000
 God promises his covenant people, which is also us as Christians,

850
01:03:33,000 --> 01:03:42,000
 we're in the new covenant, that he loves us, that he's with us, that he's faithful.

851
01:03:42,000 --> 01:03:45,000
 And so we call on this, "Lord, you say you're faithful.

852
01:03:45,000 --> 01:03:51,000
 You love us. Do something.

853
01:03:51,000 --> 01:03:56,000
 Show me that this is real." That's what we're saying.

854
01:03:56,000 --> 01:03:59,000
 And verse 5 kind of cracks me up,

855
01:03:59,000 --> 01:04:05,000
 because David is making an argument why God should deliver him.

856
01:04:05,000 --> 01:04:09,000
 He's basically saying, "I'm dead. Who can praise you?

857
01:04:09,000 --> 01:04:12,000
 What good is it? You're going to lose some praise.

858
01:04:12,000 --> 01:04:16,000
 So keep me alive."

859
01:04:16,000 --> 01:04:18,000
 Let's continue in verse 6.

860
01:04:18,000 --> 01:04:22,000
 "I'm worn out from groaning.

861
01:04:22,000 --> 01:04:28,000
 All night long I flood my bed with weeping and drench my couch with tears.

862
01:04:28,000 --> 01:04:31,000
 My eyes grow weak with sorrow.

863
01:04:31,000 --> 01:04:37,000
 They fail because of all my foes."

864
01:04:37,000 --> 01:04:44,000
 So right now the psalmist, or David, is describing just what he's been experiencing.

865
01:04:44,000 --> 01:04:45,000
 It's also part of lamenting.

866
01:04:45,000 --> 01:04:51,000
 We describe what we're experiencing, what we're feeling, what's been happening.

867
01:04:51,000 --> 01:04:56,000
 And he says that he is worn out from groaning.

868
01:04:56,000 --> 01:04:59,000
 I remember being in Calcutta.

869
01:04:59,000 --> 01:05:03,000
 I volunteered at the home of the dying for Mother Teresa.

870
01:05:03,000 --> 01:05:07,000
 It's like 20 years ago.

871
01:05:07,000 --> 01:05:13,000
 And this hall was full of people who were in their last stage of their lives.

872
01:05:13,000 --> 01:05:20,000
 And Mother Teresa had organized this space so that people do not die on their own,

873
01:05:20,000 --> 01:05:24,000
 that they do die with dignity, that there's somebody with them,

874
01:05:24,000 --> 01:05:30,000
 somebody caring for them, somebody who softens their pain.

875
01:05:30,000 --> 01:05:37,000
 And I remember when I stepped in there, I mean the hall was full of groaning.

876
01:05:37,000 --> 01:05:43,000
 Just worn out from the suffering of the sickness, the illness.

877
01:05:43,000 --> 01:05:48,000
 I also am reminded of my father when he had cancer and he passed away in 2007.

878
01:05:48,000 --> 01:05:55,000
 Just the groaning when the tumors were growing and pushing on nerves.

879
01:05:55,000 --> 01:06:00,000
 So David's saying, "I'm worn out, Lord.

880
01:06:00,000 --> 01:06:06,000
 I've got nothing.

881
01:06:06,000 --> 01:06:09,000
 I have nothing.

882
01:06:09,000 --> 01:06:12,000
 I'm an empty."

883
01:06:12,000 --> 01:06:18,000
 And then it talks about the weeping and the crying.

884
01:06:18,000 --> 01:06:21,000
 Now I don't know if you've had this experience.

885
01:06:21,000 --> 01:06:26,000
 At night time, things settle down, we're not as busy, we're not as distracted.

886
01:06:26,000 --> 01:06:31,000
 And then the stuff comes up that we're carrying.

887
01:06:31,000 --> 01:06:33,000
 And then the tears start flowing.

888
01:06:33,000 --> 01:06:35,000
 We start weeping.

889
01:06:35,000 --> 01:06:38,000
 I've had that.

890
01:06:38,000 --> 01:06:45,000
 I went through a difficult, the most difficult experience of my life, 2017.

891
01:06:45,000 --> 01:06:50,000
 And almost every night I was weeping.

892
01:06:50,000 --> 01:07:02,000
 Every night tears were flowing.

893
01:07:02,000 --> 01:07:05,000
 And so we described to God what's going on.

894
01:07:05,000 --> 01:07:10,000
 Well, what's amazing when we do that, He's not scared of what we're experiencing.

895
01:07:10,000 --> 01:07:12,000
 He's not scared of what we're feeling.

896
01:07:12,000 --> 01:07:14,000
 He's not scared of our complaint.

897
01:07:14,000 --> 01:07:15,000
 God can handle it.

898
01:07:15,000 --> 01:07:18,000
 He invites us to do that.

899
01:07:18,000 --> 01:07:20,000
 People might get uncomfortable.

900
01:07:20,000 --> 01:07:28,000
 God does not get uncomfortable with your pain, with your suffering, with your struggles, with whatever's going on.

901
01:07:28,000 --> 01:07:32,000
 God is a sympathetic listener.

902
01:07:32,000 --> 01:07:35,000
 He becomes a partner in our suffering.

903
01:07:35,000 --> 01:07:44,000
 By lamenting, we move from feeling we are alone to being in dialogue with God about what is going on.

904
01:07:44,000 --> 01:07:50,000
 So instead of carrying around whatever is going on in ourselves, now we're starting to bring it to God.

905
01:07:50,000 --> 01:07:54,000
 That's actually part of the healing process, just being heard.

906
01:07:54,000 --> 01:08:04,000
 Just putting name, naming what we've been experiencing, putting a name to it.

907
01:08:04,000 --> 01:08:10,000
 And we can trust that God understands our pain, that He understands our suffering.

908
01:08:10,000 --> 01:08:15,000
 We can know that because of Jesus.

909
01:08:15,000 --> 01:08:21,000
 Pastor Ivan earlier read a scripture, talked about sharing the suffering of Jesus.

910
01:08:21,000 --> 01:08:29,000
 Jesus was betrayed by one of His disciples, so He knows betrayal.

911
01:08:29,000 --> 01:08:34,000
 He was abandoned by His disciples, where they all just left Him.

912
01:08:34,000 --> 01:08:39,000
 He was spat on, He was beaten, He was ridiculed.

913
01:08:39,000 --> 01:08:46,000
 He was physically, ultimately put to death.

914
01:08:46,000 --> 01:08:55,000
 So He understands your emotional and your physical suffering, because He has gone through it.

915
01:08:55,000 --> 01:08:58,000
 He understands.

916
01:08:58,000 --> 01:09:03,000
 A lot of times in some of my experience I felt nobody understands me.

917
01:09:03,000 --> 01:09:06,000
 But God understands you.

918
01:09:06,000 --> 01:09:15,000
 But He also went through that, dying on the cross and rising from the dead to lead us out of the suffering.

919
01:09:15,000 --> 01:09:30,000
 To turn things around, so that we can experience His healing, His forgiveness, His new life that He gives.

920
01:09:30,000 --> 01:09:33,000
 And this is something that He can give now.

921
01:09:33,000 --> 01:09:44,000
 Earlier as we were praying, I had this vision of Jesus walking around this room, laying hands on people's shoulders.

922
01:09:44,000 --> 01:09:49,000
 Just doing healing work in people's lives.

923
01:09:49,000 --> 01:09:54,000
 Just praying over us as a community.

924
01:09:54,000 --> 01:10:02,000
 So Jesus, He loves releasing His healing and His restoration of people.

925
01:10:02,000 --> 01:10:13,000
 And there are some things where God's Word also promises that they might not get fixed on this side of our lives.

926
01:10:13,000 --> 01:10:21,000
 But we have a promise that one day God will set, for those who believe in Him, for those who trust Him, He will set everything right.

927
01:10:21,000 --> 01:10:26,000
 That there will be no more tears, there will be no more pain, no more suffering.

928
01:10:26,000 --> 01:10:31,000
 You can read Revelation 21.

929
01:10:31,000 --> 01:10:34,000
 Now there's a psalm that I came across.

930
01:10:34,000 --> 01:10:36,000
 Interesting enough, it even came up in my personal reading.

931
01:10:36,000 --> 01:10:38,000
 Psalm 56, verse 8.

932
01:10:38,000 --> 01:10:41,000
 It says this, "You keep track of all my sorrows.

933
01:10:41,000 --> 01:10:44,000
 You have collected all my tears in your bottle.

934
01:10:44,000 --> 01:10:48,000
 You have recorded each one in your book."

935
01:10:48,000 --> 01:10:55,000
 God does not miss a single tear that has flowed down your face.

936
01:10:55,000 --> 01:10:58,000
 Not a single one.

937
01:10:58,000 --> 01:11:02,000
 That's how attentive He is to you.

938
01:11:02,000 --> 01:11:12,000
 In verse 7 it also says, "My eyes grow weak with sorrow."

939
01:11:12,000 --> 01:11:22,000
 Now what this means when the Psalms talk about eyes growing weak, it has to do with that they've been looking for God.

940
01:11:22,000 --> 01:11:24,000
 They've been waiting on God.

941
01:11:24,000 --> 01:11:27,000
 But they're growing tired of looking out.

942
01:11:27,000 --> 01:11:30,000
 So it's another called God act.

943
01:11:30,000 --> 01:11:37,000
 My eyes are, I can't look much longer.

944
01:11:37,000 --> 01:11:49,000
 And then to add injury to suffering, suddenly in verse 7, there's also enemies that pop up that have smart things to say to us while we're suffering.

945
01:11:49,000 --> 01:11:54,000
 Maybe it's blaming you for what's going on.

946
01:11:54,000 --> 01:11:57,000
 People always try to explain suffering.

947
01:11:57,000 --> 01:12:00,000
 And then they try to find fault somewhere.

948
01:12:00,000 --> 01:12:06,000
 And so a lot of times they put the fault on the person who's going through the suffering.

949
01:12:06,000 --> 01:12:10,000
 Maybe it's somebody taking advantage of you while you're suffering.

950
01:12:10,000 --> 01:12:16,000
 Maybe in your job or elsewhere.

951
01:12:16,000 --> 01:12:18,000
 So this just adds.

952
01:12:18,000 --> 01:12:21,000
 But let's continue reading in verse 8.

953
01:12:21,000 --> 01:12:24,000
 It says this, "Away from me, all you who do evil.

954
01:12:24,000 --> 01:12:26,000
 For the Lord has heard my weeping.

955
01:12:26,000 --> 01:12:28,000
 The Lord has heard my cry for mercy.

956
01:12:28,000 --> 01:12:30,000
 The Lord accepts my prayer.

957
01:12:30,000 --> 01:12:34,000
 All my enemies will be overwhelmed with shame and anguish.

958
01:12:34,000 --> 01:12:40,000
 They will turn back and suddenly be put to shame."

959
01:12:40,000 --> 01:12:48,000
 So suddenly God's unfailing love, this love that David called for in verse 4, breaks into the situation.

960
01:12:48,000 --> 01:12:50,000
 David has been hurt.

961
01:12:50,000 --> 01:12:52,000
 God has heard the complaint.

962
01:12:52,000 --> 01:12:54,000
 He has heard the mourning.

963
01:12:54,000 --> 01:12:57,000
 And that changes everything.

964
01:12:57,000 --> 01:12:59,000
 This is a turnaround.

965
01:12:59,000 --> 01:13:02,000
 This is a turning point.

966
01:13:02,000 --> 01:13:10,000
 Now we don't know how much time has passed between the lamenting and this line.

967
01:13:10,000 --> 01:13:14,000
 A lot of times, sometimes God meets us immediately.

968
01:13:14,000 --> 01:13:18,000
 Sometimes there's a longer period.

969
01:13:18,000 --> 01:13:20,000
 But don't be discouraged.

970
01:13:20,000 --> 01:13:24,000
 Jesus is at work underneath the surface.

971
01:13:24,000 --> 01:13:26,000
 He is working.

972
01:13:26,000 --> 01:13:28,000
 Don't lose hope.

973
01:13:28,000 --> 01:13:29,000
 Hold on.

974
01:13:29,000 --> 01:13:33,000
 He's at work in your life.

975
01:13:33,000 --> 01:13:38,000
 And then suddenly, you know, His word will break through, His assurance.

976
01:13:38,000 --> 01:13:40,000
 We don't know what happened.

977
01:13:40,000 --> 01:13:42,000
 Did God speak to David?

978
01:13:42,000 --> 01:13:45,000
 Did somebody have a word for him, come for him?

979
01:13:45,000 --> 01:13:49,000
 Was he encouraged through some of scripture?

980
01:13:49,000 --> 01:13:53,000
 We don't know.

981
01:13:53,000 --> 01:13:57,000
 Now I've had an experience like that.

982
01:13:57,000 --> 01:14:01,000
 I shared earlier that I've gone through a very difficult time.

983
01:14:01,000 --> 01:14:07,000
 And I went to, attended a church and was worshipping.

984
01:14:07,000 --> 01:14:09,000
 And I was stuck.

985
01:14:09,000 --> 01:14:12,000
 I did not know how to move forward in my life.

986
01:14:12,000 --> 01:14:19,000
 I -- my life had come to a sudden halt.

987
01:14:19,000 --> 01:14:21,000
 I was hopeless.

988
01:14:21,000 --> 01:14:24,000
 I just really did not know what to do.

989
01:14:24,000 --> 01:14:30,000
 And I really didn't care even what happened to me at that point.

990
01:14:30,000 --> 01:14:34,000
 And so as I was worshipping, I had a word from Jesus.

991
01:14:34,000 --> 01:14:36,000
 And I've shared this here before.

992
01:14:36,000 --> 01:14:41,000
 I'm not finished with you yet.

993
01:14:41,000 --> 01:14:43,000
 But I felt like He was.

994
01:14:43,000 --> 01:14:46,000
 I felt like it was over.

995
01:14:46,000 --> 01:14:48,000
 He said, "I'm not finished with you yet."

996
01:14:48,000 --> 01:14:51,000
 Now, were all my problems resolved in that moment?

997
01:14:51,000 --> 01:14:52,000
 No.

998
01:14:52,000 --> 01:14:57,000
 I still was in the same situation, but I was heard.

999
01:14:57,000 --> 01:15:06,000
 Because God had spoken to me in my lamenting and my crying and in my worshipping Him.

1000
01:15:06,000 --> 01:15:12,000
 And it released hope and courage to move forward.

1001
01:15:12,000 --> 01:15:18,000
 Suddenly my perspective had changed.

1002
01:15:18,000 --> 01:15:27,000
 And then God bit by bit turned my life around and just poured His goodness and His love on me.

1003
01:15:27,000 --> 01:15:29,000
 So this is the transformative part.

1004
01:15:29,000 --> 01:15:34,000
 When we bring our pains, our complaints, our sorrows to God in a prayer of lament,

1005
01:15:34,000 --> 01:15:40,000
 that God, one way or another, at one point or another, that He meets us, that He speaks to us,

1006
01:15:40,000 --> 01:15:44,000
 that He provides for us what we need to move forward,

1007
01:15:44,000 --> 01:15:50,000
 to know His steadfast love in the circumstances that we're facing,

1008
01:15:50,000 --> 01:15:58,000
 to know that He is going to see us through.

1009
01:15:58,000 --> 01:16:00,000
 Now, at the beginning of the message, I asked the question,

1010
01:16:00,000 --> 01:16:06,000
 "How can we bring our sorrows, grief and pain before God?"

